{{Infobox language |name = Zo'é |nativename = Poturu, Poturujara, Buré |pronunciation = |states = [[Brazil]] |region = [[Pará]], Obidos Municipality, Cuminapanema River |ethnicity=[[Zo'é people|Zo'é]] |speakers = 150 |date=1998 |ref=e18 |familycolor = American |fam1 = [[Tupian languages|Tupian]] |fam2 = [[Tupi–Guarani]] |fam3 = Wayampí |iso3 = pto |glotto = zoee1240 |glottorefname = Zo'é }}
'''Zo'é''' (Jo'é) is spoken by the indigenous [[Zo'é people]] of [[Pará]], [[Brazil]]. It is close to the [[Emerillon language]].
Zo'é is also known as Buré, Poturu, Poturujara, and Tupí of Cunimapanema.<ref name=e18/>
